results.name: Number of ordered triples of positive integers summing to n, any two of which have a common divisor > 1.
comment: The first relatively prime triple (15,10,6) is counted under a(31).
link: Fausto A. C. Cariboni, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
example: The a(6) = 1 through a(15) = 7 triples (empty columns indicated by dots, A = 10):
xref: A014311 intersected with A337666 ranks these compositions.
A337667 counts these compositions of any length.
A335402 lists the positions of zeros.
A337461 is the coprime instead of non-coprime version.
A337599 is the unordered version, with strict case A337605.
A101268 counts pairwise coprime or singleton compositions.
A200976 and A328673 count pairwise non-relatively prime partitions.
A318717 counts pairwise non-coprime strict partitions.
